Thinking Data First

1.
Courses

title: string [unique, present]
description: text [present]

has_many lessons


Lessons

title: string [unique, present]
body: text [present]
course_id: integer [present]

belongs_to course


2.
Users

username: string [unique, 4-12 chars, present]
email: string [unique, present]
password: string [unique, 6-16 chars, present]

has_one profile


Profiles

city: string [present]
state: string [present]
country: string [present]
age: integer [1-3 digits, present]
gender: string ['male' or 'female', present]
user_id: integer [present]

belongs_to user


3.
Users
username: string [unique, 4-12 chars, present]
email: string [unique, present]
password: string [unique, 6-16 chars, present]

has_many pins
has_many comments


Pins

url: string [present]
user_id: integer [present]

belongs_to user
has_many comments


Comments
body: text [present]
user_id: integer [present]
pin_id: integer [present]

belongs_to user
belongs_to pin


4.
Users
username: string [unique, 4-12 chars, present]
email: string [unique, present]
password: string [unique, 6-16 chars, present]

has_many posts
has_many comments


Posts

url: string [present]
user_id: integer [present]

belongs_to user
has_many comments


Comments
body: text [present]
user_id: integer [present]
heirarchy: integer [present]
	if heirarchy = 0
		post_id: integer [present]
		belongs_to post
	else
		comment_id: integer [present]
		belongs_to comment

belongs_to user
has_many comments